In this paper, discrete transformers are adopted to verify the feasibility of the proposed structure. Although the integrated transformer can improve efficiency and power density, it is very difficult to design the integrated magnetics using single EE or EIR cores [

 18

]. In particular, the integrated core of the high-frequency three-phase for high-power applications is expensive. The performance and functionality of the discrete transformer are not different from the integrated one in terms of the proposed hybrid modulation algorithm. In the case of the transformer connection of the 3P-DAB converter, the Y–Y structure is used to reduce the imbalance of the phase current when compared with Y–Δ/Δ–Y connections [

 19

].
